{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e58f5824-2021-482e-ba9b-d936f766ffdb","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n1. **Update NuGet packages:**\n   - Keep `NUnit` and `NUnit3TestAdapter` (≥ 4.6.0 already supports it).\n   - **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk`.\n   - **Add** `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` and `NUnit.Extension.MicrosoftTestingPlatform`.\n\n2. **Update your `.csproj`:**\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>          <!-- required -->\n     <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n3. **Run tests with:**\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run          # direct execution\n   dotnet test         # also works with TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport\n   ```\n\nThe key difference: your test project becomes an executable. `EnableMSTestRunner` (despite the name) enables the Microsoft.Testing.Platform entry point for NUnit too.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc0335e9-563c-4ac3-b6ba-860ccfe928d6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a general knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":337,"requestId":"340B:37A92F:72507F1:7E9D3DA:69F3FA00"},"id":"b0ae2ffa-5877-4a4c-9710-f54f24a85838","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:55:36.144Z","parentId":"667b339e-9848-4704-b4a0-57e5235097d2"}
